This paper deals with privacy attacks on smart home devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning algorithms for detecting and identifying IoT devices and their actions suggests that this paper may also belong to the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of wireless communication protocols such as WiFi, ZigBee, and BLE suggests that this paper may also belong to the categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
